reviewText: Good set for me

A thousand times YESSSSS!!!  All of these great movies on one order - what can beat that?  Thanks TCM for putting this out!  This includes Yankee Doodle Dandy, Thank Your Lucky Stars, Hollywood Canteen (one I have wanted to find and watch for many years), and This Is The Army.  Enjoy these top-notch movies, and thanks again TCM for putting them all together!!

My mother met a popular actor at a USO and they were wartime sweethearts... his name shall remain anonymous.  I met his son, by the woman he finally met and married, as did my Mother meet a wonderful man who was my step then adopted Dad.  His son and I made our partners nervous cause they suspected us of some kind of hanky panky, he and I had never met before, I feel after learning some years after of the love affair between our parents was the bond that was the connection.  There is no other reason.  I love having this secret and old movies give me a chance to see my almost step dad...

You can read other reviews posted ahead of mine and essentially all of us love the four movie presentations but the packaging leaves so much to be desired.  The pack features one spindle with all four discs compressed together, I'm amazed that each one played well.  But this is no way to treat these wonderful classics and I will immediately relocate each disc to a separate pack in order to best preserve them.  Here's my individual ratings:
Hollywood Canteen - ***** Outstanding, delighted in the love story between Robert Hutton and Joan Leslie though far-fetched
Yankee Doodle Dandy - ***** Another outstanding movie, surely one of the best for the two lead characters, Cagney and Leslie
Thank Your Lucky Stars - **** Goofy but entertaining with Leslie, Cantor, and Morgan
This is the Army - *** Definitely a WWII propaganda film but well done featuring Reagan and Leslie
The film extras were worth the price alone! Includes period cartoons and newsreels.
